<p>On top of that, the bolded part is a subversion of the joke &quot;look at this good person who has a dark and immoral secret&quot;. It works as a pithy joke in the Personnel Dossier because we expect Ambrose to be immoral, and that sentence turns the concept on its head and says &quot;no, he's actually quite moral!&quot;</p>
